I made a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva, which is an easy-to-use online design tool. It helped me create a neat and attractive poster even without having advanced design skills.

The infographic is called “Digital Literacy Basics,” and it focuses on explaining what digital literacy is and why it’s important for students. It includes topics like the meaning of digital literacy, common digital tools students use, and tips for staying safe online. I also added points about using strong passwords, being careful on the internet, and communicating respectfully online.

While designing it, I tried to keep everything simple, colorful, and easy to understand. I used different sections and icons to make the information more interesting and clear for anyone reading it.
